# Read the CSV from URL
diabetes <- read.csv(file_url)

# View the first few rows
# head(diabetes)

# Drop Outcome (not used for inference)
diabetes$Outcome <- NULL

# Replace 0s with NA in invalid physiological variables
na_vars <- c("Glucose", "BloodPressure", "SkinThickness", "Insulin", "BMI")
diabetes[na_vars] <- lapply(diabetes[na_vars], function(x) ifelse(x == 0, NA, x))

# Drop rows with NA
diabetes_clean <- na.omit(diabetes)

# Log-transform skewed variables
diabetes_clean$log_Insulin <- log1p(diabetes_clean$Insulin)
diabetes_clean$log_SkinThickness <- log1p(diabetes_clean$SkinThickness)

# Pairwise plot
ggpairs(diabetes_clean[, c("Glucose", "Pregnancies", "BloodPressure", "BMI", 
                           "Age", "DiabetesPedigreeFunction", "log_Insulin", 
                           "log_SkinThickness")])


# Full model
lm_full <- lm(Glucose ~ Pregnancies + BloodPressure + BMI + Age +
                DiabetesPedigreeFunction + log_Insulin + log_SkinThickness,
              data = diabetes_clean)

# Exhaustive subset selection
exhaustive <- regsubsets(Glucose ~ Pregnancies + BloodPressure + BMI + Age +
                           DiabetesPedigreeFunction + log_Insulin + log_SkinThickness,
                         data = diabetes_clean, nvmax = 7, method = "exhaustive")

# Summary
ex_summary <- summary(exhaustive)

# Plot Mallows Cp and Adjusted R
par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
plot(ex_summary$cp, type = "b", xlab = "Number of Predictors", ylab = "Cp", main = "Mallow's Cp")
plot(ex_summary$adjr2, type = "b", xlab = "Number of Predictors", ylab = "Adjusted R", main = "Adjusted R")

                    log_Insulin, data = diabetes_clean)

# Summary

# Create a function to extract variable names for each subset
get_model_formula <- function(model_id, regfit, response = "Glucose") {
  vars <- names(coef(regfit, model_id))[-1]  # exclude intercept
  formula <- as.formula(paste(response, "~", paste(vars, collapse = " + ")))
  return(formula)
}

# 2. Loop over all subset sizes and fit lm + calculate AIC
aic_results <- data.frame(ModelSize = integer(), AIC = numeric(), Formula = character())

for (i in 1:7) {
  fmla <- get_model_formula(i, exhaustive)
  model <- lm(fmla, data = diabetes_clean)
  aic_results <- rbind(aic_results, data.frame(ModelSize = i, AIC = AIC(model), Formula = as.character(fmla)))
}

# 3. Sort by AIC
aic_results <- aic_results[order(aic_results$AIC), ]
print(aic_results)

library(leaps)

# Exhaustive subset selection (already done earlier)
exhaustive <- regsubsets(Glucose ~ Pregnancies + BloodPressure + BMI + Age +
                         DiabetesPedigreeFunction + log_Insulin + log_SkinThickness,
                         data = diabetes_clean, nvmax = 7, method = "exhaustive")

# Get summary with Adjusted R
ex_summary <- summary(exhaustive)

# Function to extract model formula from regsubsets object
get_model_formula <- function(model_id, regfit_obj, response = "Glucose") {
  vars <- names(coef(regfit_obj, model_id))[-1]  # exclude intercept
  as.formula(paste(response, "~", paste(vars, collapse = " + ")))
}

# Collect Adjusted R and AIC for each best model
results <- data.frame(ModelSize = integer(), Adjusted_R2 = numeric(), AIC = numeric())

for (i in 1:7) {
  formula_i <- get_model_formula(i, exhaustive)
  model_i <- lm(formula_i, data = diabetes_clean)
  results <- rbind(results, data.frame(
    ModelSize = i,
    Adjusted_R2 = ex_summary$adjr2[i],
    AIC = AIC(model_i)
  ))
}

# Print result table
print(results)
NA
# Step 1: Fit the full model
lm_full <- lm(Glucose ~ Pregnancies + BloodPressure + BMI + Age +
                DiabetesPedigreeFunction + log_Insulin + log_SkinThickness,
              data = diabetes_clean)

# Step 2: Calculate Cook's Distance
cooks_d <- cooks.distance(lm_full)

k <- length(coef(lm_full))  # number of beta parameters (including intercept)
n <- nrow(diabetes_clean)
threshold <- (2 * k) / n

# Step 4: Identify influential points
influential_points <- which(cooks_d > threshold)

diabetes_no_influential <- diabetes_clean[!influential, ]

# Step 5: Refit model without influential observations
lm_cooks_cleaned <- lm(Glucose ~ BloodPressure + Age +
                           log_Insulin,
                       data = diabetes_no_influential)

# Step 6: Show summary and diagnostic plots
summary(lm_cooks_cleaned)

# After fitting your final model
model <- lm(Glucose ~ BloodPressure + Age + log_Insulin,
            data = diabetes_clean)

# Cook's Distance
cooksD <- cooks.distance(model)

# Set threshold
k <- length(coef(model))  # number of parameters
n <- nrow(diabetes_clean)
threshold <- 2 * k / n

# Identify influential observations
influential_points <- which(cooksD > threshold)

# Refit model without those points
model_cleaned <- lm(Glucose ~ BloodPressure + Age + log_Insulin,
                    data = diabetes_clean[-influential_points, ])

# Compare both models
summary(model)
